      • calculateShare

        public static void calculateShare(int[] regionraster,
                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,float[]> shares,
                                  java.lang.Integer mapID,
                                  float[] speciesraster,
                                  float speciesNodata,
                                  float regionNodata,
                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer>>> efiscenIDs)
        Calculates shares and stores them to a HashMap. Also extra relations are removed from efiscenIDs. Shares are calculated by dividing the individual raster cell share by total percentage of species per region. About extra relations: Some species may contain relations from that have no data for particular regions in species raster. Such mappings are deleted from efiscenIDs, so that result calculations will be accurate.
        Parameters:
        regionraster - Raster with all the regions.
        shares - HashMap to which shares are stored.
        mapID - Map id for species raster. Shares are stored to map shares by map id.
        speciesraster - Species raster.
        speciesNodata - No data value for species map.
        regionNodata - No data value for region map.
        efiscenIDs - HashMap containing relations from database. Maps that do not have data for regions are removed from the relations map.

      • calculateShare

        public static void calculateShare(RasterCompressor.CompressedRasterFloat speciesraster,
                                  RasterCompressor.CompressedRasterInt regionraster,
                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,RasterCompressor.CompressedRasterFloat> shares,
                                  java.lang.Integer mapID,

                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer>>> efiscenIDs)
        Calculates shares and stores them to a HashMap. Also extra relations are removed from efiscenIDs. Shares are calculated by dividing the individual raster cell share by total percentage of species per region. About extra relations: Some species may contain relations from that have no data for particular regions in species raster. Such mappings are deleted from efiscenIDs, so that result calculations will be accurate.
        Parameters:
        speciesraster - Species raster that shares are calculated for
        regionraster - Raster containing regions.
        shares - HashMap where calculated shares are stored.
        mapID - ID for this species raster. Share raster is stored to HashMap shares by this ID.
        speciesNodata - No data value for species raster.
        regionNodata - Nodata value for region raster.
        efiscenIDs - HashMap containing relations from database. Maps that do not have data for regions are removed from the relations map.

      • calculateResults

        public static RasterCompressor.CompressedRasterFloat calculateResults(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,RasterCompressor.CompressedRasterFloat> shares,
                                                                      RasterCompressor.CompressedRasterInt regions,
                                                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Float>> efiscenValues,
                                                                      float nodata,
                                                                      java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer>>> efiscenIDs)
        Calculates the final result raster. Multiplies area shares for species by efiscen variable. Value for area = Share of species * value / number of relations for species
        Parameters:
        shares - Previously calculated shares.
        regions - Rasters containing regions.
        efiscenValues - Values to be disaggregated.
        nodata - Nodata value for rasters.
        efiscenIDs - Relations from database.
        Returns:
        Raster containing the disaggregated results.
